# Testing Standards

## Framework
- xUnit + FluentValidation.TestHelper for validators
- `WebApplicationFactory<Program>` for API integration tests
- Use `Testing` environment + InMemory DB via `DatabaseProvider=InMemory`

## Unit tests (Application.Tests)
- Test validators: valid command passes; each rule has a failing case
- Test `RolePermissionMatrix` with `[Theory]` + `[InlineData]`
- Test encryption/security helpers with deterministic inputs
- Name tests: `Should_{Expected}_When_{Condition}`

## Integration tests (Api.Tests)
- Register mock `IComputeProvider` / `IPodProvider` in `ConfigureTestServices`
- Use `NoOpPodNotificationService` when SignalR is not under test
- Flow: register → authenticate → act → assert status + response body
- Assert secrets never appear in response JSON (`DoesNotContain("ApiKey")`)

## What to test
- Behavior and HTTP contracts — not implementation details
- Permission gates return 403 for unauthorized roles
- End-to-end: create → operate → delete for each major resource

## What to avoid
- Tests that only assert `NotNull` without checking values
- Hitting real RunPod/external APIs in CI — always mock providers
- Shared mutable state between tests; use unique InMemory DB names per factory

## Run commands
```bash
dotnet test tests/PodPilot.Application.Tests
dotnet test tests/PodPilot.Api.Tests
```
